article.headline: Austin Peay 60, SE Missouri State 50
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Zac Schlader scored 25 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead Austin Peay to a 60-50 victory over Southeast Missouri in the Ohio Valley Conference opener for both teams Thursday night. William Durden and Maurice Hampton both chipped in with 10 points for the Governors (3-10, 1-0), who shot 44.8 percent from the field. The Redhawks (5-7, 0-1) pulled to within four points twice in the second half, the final time coming with 6:15 left and Austin Peay leading 42-38. But the Governors answered with a 6-0 run capped by a Hampton jumper to lead 48-38 with 4:59 to play. The Governors jumped out to a quick 8-0 lead and stretched their advantage to 25-13 with 3:47 left in the first half on a layup by Levi Carmichael. Austin Peay led 27-18 at halftime. Reggie Golson led Southeast Missouri with 18 points and nine rebounds, and Dainmon Gonner had 16 points. The Redhawks shot 42.9 percent from the field.
